<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        CAB REMOVAL AND INSTALLATION - INSTALL CAB
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>INSTALL CAB</title>
        <para>The following steps can be used as a guide. Refer to the appropriate section in the CTS- 5000 Master
            service manual.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With cab secured to lifting fixture and hoist, proceed as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install cab front mounting hinge pins.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install cab lift rams to cab.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Position cab safety prop and engage prop.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove cab lifting fixture from cab.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect brake air lines and hoses.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect engine shut-off control cable.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect clutch.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect heater hoses.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect wiring harness from connectors under cab right floor panel and all other wiring
                leading from the chassis or engine into the cab.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect accelerator linkage and cruise control (if so equipped).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install steering gear universal joint at steering gear.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect battery ground cable.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fill radiator and close air tank valves.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect A/C lines and charge system if applicable.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check all air and fluid connections for leaks.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lower, raise and lower cab to check operation.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Road test vehicle for proper operation.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
